 place, except for what tall tales and wild stories try to convey. Hence, folklore of the area has it that the valley is inhabited by lizard-like monsters, fearsome flying serpents, giant snakes and evil crocodiles. Other stories speak of ˜cannibal savages, blood-thirsty catmen and degenerate snakemen. However, there is a legend that is intriguing: apparently, a secret city of the lost Lankharhan empire is said to lie deep within the Forgotten Valley. But that remains to be proven."        ˝"The elven forest-kingdom of Lorill is almost four thousand years old. Although these elves are peaceful, they are quite defensive of their borders. Thus, they allow passage into their kingdom only to trade caravans or to people accompanied by a subject  ¯of the kingdom. Not even other elves are allowed, unless escorted by a native of Lorill. On the other hand, elves from Lorill often wander about outside of their kingdom. In any case, Lorill trades actively with Seacrest, Calember and the gnomes of       ÛGoldylock, but remain fierce isolationists. This is probably due to the fact that their forest-kingdom is bordered to the north by the Scales Swamps and is often plagued by raids from trolls: not wishing to leave themselves open to invasion by            ˆhumans lords and kings, they prefer to close their borders as prevention. Indeed, although peace and prosperity reigns today between Lorill and its human neighbors, some of the older monarchs of Seacrest attempted to conquer the elves in the past         …- and thus Lorill remains extremely wary to this day, knowing that the succeeding short lives of humans are all too often harbingers of quick changes in disposition and goodwill towards their kingdom."                                                      ˚"Librunae is a local folklore hero of note. This good witch was shunned most of her life by folks, ignorance and fear overlooking her good principles and devotion to help others. Ten years ago, the black dragon known as 'Bla